<book id="ejb-jpa">
    <bookinfo>
        <title>JPA Server-Side Deployment</title>
        <issuenum>${content.version}</issuenum>
        <pubdate>${docbook.pubdate}</pubdate>
        <copyright>
            <year>${copyright.year}</year>
            <holder>${copyright.holder}</holder>
        </copyright>
        <abstract>
            <para>This presentation provides coverage of how to package a JPA persistence unit
                 within an EJB or WAR deployed to the server. It covers the resources involved
                 and how they can be injected into the beans of the data tier as well as various
                 issues that can arise and suggested solutions. 
            </para>
        </abstract>
    </bookinfo>
    <preface id="jpa-serverside-purpose">
        <title>Purpose</title>
        <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
            <listitem><para>Server-side Resources</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>EJB and WAR deployment</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Resource injection</para></listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </preface>

